The course covers fundamental aspects of Old Slavic and Old Russian language, including reading and analysis of texts spanning different historical periods. It also explores the development of the modern Russian literary language and its stylistic framework.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide students with an understanding of the historical evolution of literary and written language across various epochs in Russia, spanning from the emergence of writing to the creation of the modern literary language. Additionally, it aims to illustrate the significance of the Church Slavonic language in shaping the Russian literary language. The course integrates insights from sociolinguistics, cultural history, and historical stylistics to underscore the interconnectedness between the history of the literary language and key sociocultural concepts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course,
Upon completion of the course, students will have a general understanding of the structure of Old Slavonic and Old Russian language. Students will demonstrate proficiency in reading and analyzing texts from diverse historical periods, discerning the role of Slavonic elements across different genres. Furthermore, students will be able to effectively employ these elements in the creation of modern texts across various functional styles.
